definition.value: An Ontology to represents the Reference Architecture Model for Industry 4.0 (RAMI), including the concept of the Administration Shell I4.0 Component.

comment.en: A set of data elements that describe object attributes. These attributes need to refer to a data element within an existing submodel.
A key is a reference to an element by its id.

comment.en: An Asset describes meta data of an asset that is represented by an AAS.nThe asset may either represent an asset type or an asset instance.nThe asset has a globally unique identifier plus – if needed – additional domain specific (proprietary) identifiers.
A property is a data element that has a single value.
Element that can have data specification templates. A template defines the additional attributes an element may or shall have.
An element that is referable by its idShort. This id is not globally unique. This id is unique within the name space of the element.
Container for security relevant information of the AAS.

A Submodel defines a specific aspect of the asset represented by the AAS.nA submodel is used to structure the virtual representation and technical functionality of an Administration Shell into distinguishable parts. Each submodel refers to a well-defined domain or subject matter.nSubmodels can become standardized and thus become submodels types. Submodels can have different life-cycles.
A submodel element is an element suitable for the description and differentiation of assets.
An element with a kind is an element that can either represent a type or an instance. Default for an element is that it is representing an instance.
A File is a data element that represents a file via its path description.
Element that can have data specification templates. A template defines the additional attributes an element may or shall have.

A data element is a submodel element that is not further composed out of other submodel elements. A data element is a submodel element that has a value. The type of value differs for different subtypes of data elements.
An operation is a submodel element with input and output variables.

description.en: "The AAS itself can also define its own dictionary that contains semantic definitions of its submodel elements. These semantic definitions are called concept descriptions (ConceptDescription). It is optional whether an AAS defines its own concept dictionary (ConceptDictionary) or not."

comment.en: A BLOB is a data element that represents a file that is contained with its source code in the value attribute.

description.en: A reference element is a data element that defines a reference to another element within the same or another AAS or a reference to an external object or entity.

comment.en: The RAMI4.0 model features one, generalized life-cycle axis, which was derived from IEC 62890. The basic idea is to distinguish for all assets within Industrie 4.0 between possible types and instance. This makes it possible to apply thentype/instance distinction for all elements such as material type/material instance, product type/product instance, machine type/ machine instance and more. Business related information will be handled on the 'Business' layer of thenRAMI4.0 model, as well, covering also order details and workflows, again with types/ instances.

The RAMI4.0 model features one, generalized life-cycle axis, which was derived from IEC 62890. The basic idea is to distinguish for all assets within Industrie 4.0 between possible types and instance. This makes it possible to apply the type/instance distinction for all elements such as material type/material instance, product type/product instance, machine type/ machine instance and more. Business related information will be handled on the 'Business' layer of thenRAMI4.0 model, as well, covering also order details and workflows, again with types/ instances.
Different views associated to the Administration Shell via the Submodels
An element that has a globally unique identifier.

A dictionary contains elements that can be reused. The concept dictionary contains concept descriptions. Typically a concept description dictionary of an AAS contains only concept descriptions of elements used within submodels of the AAS.

description.en: An operation variable is a submodel element that is used as input or output variable of an operation.

definition.value: Each order for manufacturing runs through a life cycle and its specifics necessarily have an impact on the production facility during performance of the order

description.en: The qualifier value is the value of the qualifier.nConstraint AASd-006: if both, the value and the valueId are present then the value needs to be identical to the short name of the referenced coded value in qualifierValueId.
A qualifier is a type-value pair that makes additional statements w.r.t. the value of the element.
A formula is used to describe constraints by a logical expression.

comment.en: Every Identifiable may have administrative information. In later versions additional attributes may be added.
